1190231605.text: "In these studies, PTX-2 increased phosphorylation of Cdc25C and decreased protein levels of Cdc2 (Cdk1, cyclin dependent kinase 1), cyclin B1; and the M phase specific marker protein, phospho-histone 3 was markedly increased by PTX-2 [XREF_BIBR]."
